public interface Expression
extends ExpressionType, java.lang.Cloneable

Repredent any expression that can be evaluated. Expressions can be of several different kinds:

  • AryExpression: an expression with two predicates, as for example AND
  • UnaryExpression: an expression with one predicate, as for example NOT
  • Variable: a Variable
  • Constant: a Constant

getParentBlock

CodeBlock getParentBlock()
Return the parent expression block if the expression is one of several expressions separated by commas. For example, in the following equation: b=a+2; return b, the two "b=a+2" and "return b" have "b=a+2; return b" as their parent block.

evalAsInt

int evalAsInt()
Evaluate the expression as an int. The result of the evaluation will be the same as eval(), but the evaluation engine will be able to optimize the computation by knwoing that the result is an int (primitive valeus are cached internally).

evalAsFloat

float evalAsFloat()
Evaluate the expression as a float. The result of the evaluation will be the same as eval(), but the evaluation engine will be able to optimize the computation by knwoing that the result is a float (primitive valeus are cached internally).

evalAsBoolean

boolean evalAsBoolean()
Evaluate the expression as a boolean. The result of the evaluation will be the same as eval(), but the evaluation engine will be able to optimize the computation by knwoing that the result is a boolean (primitive valeus are cached internally).

eval

java.lang.Object eval()

getResultType

short getResultType()
Return the type of the result for the expression. The type can be:
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_INTEGER: integer
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_FLOAT: float
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_NUMERIC: integer or float value. The runtime actual type may depend on the expression arguments
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_STRING: string
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_DYNAMIC: dynamic type. The runtime actual type may depend on the expression arguments
  • ExpressionType.TYPE_UNDEF: undefined type. The default type, characteristic of an error if entountered.

getResultStructure

short getResultStructure()
Return the structure of the result for the expression. The structure can be:
  • ExpressionType.STRUCT_SCALAR: a scalar value
  • ExpressionType.STRUCT_ARRAY: an array value

getExpressionName

java.lang.String getExpressionName()
Return the expression name.

getVariables

java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Variable> getVariables()
Return the variables declared by this expression. Note that this methos will not return any internal variables used by the expression. For example, in the following expression: int c=a+b, only "a" and "b" will be returned.

getVariable
